    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix GUTI identity type not set in NAS registration messages\n\n### Summary\nThe `fill_guti` function in the NR UE NAS module was not setting the `typeofidentity` field when constructing GUTI-based mobile identity structures. This caused the UE to send registration requests with GUTI identities that had an uninitialized identity type field, leading to AMF rejecting the registration with cause #23 (\\\"Invalid mandatory information\\\").\n\nThe issue manifested as UEs failing to register when attempting to use a stored GUTI instead of SUCI, with registration attempts timing out or being rejected by the network. The problem was particularly evident after UE reboots or when resuming from idle state.\n\nRoot cause was the missing initialization of `mi->guti.typeofidentity` in the `fill_guti` function, while all other similar functions (`fill_suci`, `fill_fgstmsi`, etc.) properly set their respective identity type fields.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/nr_nas_msg.c`: Added missing `mi->guti.typeofidentity = FGS_MOBILE_IDENTITY_5G_GUTI;` initialization in `fill_guti` function to match the pattern used by other mobile identity construction functions.\n"
}